Defendant Michael Ray Raspberry in court with attorney Lisa M Schlieben.  Defendant Michael Ray Raspberry in custody.  Jay R Pucek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  As part of negotiations, the State moved Wauwatosa Police Incident Report #11-025599 as a read in; Court observed and granted same to be read in on this case.  Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms. Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.   The Court imposed the following sentence:
Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 4 years  consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2 years. Defendant shall serve 2 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION. The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample unless previously provided.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay the DNA sucharge, costs and disbursements to be collected by DOC not to exceed 25%.  Balance to be paid while on extended supervision.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - Undergo a mental health evaluation; follow thru with any treatment recommended;
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed by a duly licensed physician for his mental or physical needs;
 - No alcohol;
 - Urine screens;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - No contact with No. #1 Chinese Restaurant on 6119 West North Avenue, city of Wauwatosa, county of Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - No contact with Golden Chicken, 2532 West Wisconsin Avenue, city and county of Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - Pay any balance remaining of the surcharges, costs and disbursements; pay supervision fees.  Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
